      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's the thing though, i haven't even had a security breach. my passwords are fine and no one logged in. it feels more like the identity itself has just... been detached from me. like the \"me\" that lives online is running on its own now, doing things I'd never do but in my exact voice. it's like i'm watching a version of myself that's more \"me\" than i am. how can something be that precise if it isn't actually me living through those accounts?",
